conclusion: Understanding interaction between objects in a 3D environment.
Objects are placed on a table, task is to determine sequence of events when objects A and B move and land.
Objects A and B are positioned on the table with arrows indicating their movement through the air.
Objects A and B will collide with existing objects on the table when they land.
Objects will first collide with objects they are initially placed on, then with other objects on the table.
Objects on the table will move to new positions due to collision.
